			<h1 class="singlePageTitle">We must do more to save children from scourge of conflict says UN envoy</h1>

					
		
                                                        <span class="featuredPostMeta">

                                                                <!-- added by eric -->
                                                                <a onclick="setNewPlaylist(900,'http://downloads.unmultimedia.org/radio/en/ltd/mp3/2013/f-syria-children4page.mp3', 'V2UgbXVzdCBkbyBtb3JlIHRvIHNhdmUgY2hpbGRyZW4gZnJvbSBzY291cmdlIG9mIGNvbmZsaWN0IHNheXMgVU4gZW52b3k=', 'http://www.unmultimedia.org/radio/english/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/syrian-children2.gif')">Listen</a> /
<script type="text/javascript">document.write(createDownloadLink('en','http://downloads.unmultimedia.org/radio/en/ltd/mp3/2013/f-syria-children4page.mp3?save','Download'))</script>
                                                                <!-- /added by eric -->

                                                        </span>

					
	
			<!-- post_excerpt --><!-- /post_excerpt --><div id="attachment_207909" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 360px"><a href="http://www.unmultimedia.org/radio/english/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/syrian-children2.gif"><img class="size-full wp-image-207909" title="syrian-children2" src="http://www.unmultimedia.org/radio/english/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/syrian-children2.gif" alt="" width="350" height="300" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">The park's playground teems with newly arrived Syrian refugee children. UNHCR/S. Baldwin</p></div>
<p>As the war in Syria continues unabated, children continue to bear the brunt of the conflict, says the Secretary-General's Special Representative for Children and Armed Conflict.</p>
<p>Leila Zerrougi, on a recent visit to Syria, met with many children and their families who expressed the horrors of the conflict, their fears and their preoccupation for their children's loss of education.</p>
<p>Beng Poblete-Enriquez has the story.</p>
<p>Duration: 3&#8217;12&#8243;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div class="clear"></div>			
						
			<div class="clear"></div>

			
			
                                        
                                         


